From what you've shared, it sounds like you're experiencing some difficulty with reading and might be consuming caffeine (coffee). Since these symptoms have only been present for three days, and you don't have any significant medical history or medications, this could be related to a few common issues.

Excessive caffeine intake can sometimes cause jitters, difficulty concentrating, and vision issues. Additionally, prolonged reading or screen time without proper breaks can lead to eye strain and reading difficulties.

Here are my suggestions:
- Try cutting back on coffee for a few days to see if it helps
- Take regular breaks when reading (try the 20-20-20 rule: every 20 minutes, look at something 20 feet away for 20 seconds)
- Ensure you're getting enough sleep
- Make sure you have good lighting when reading

If symptoms persist beyond a week or get worse, it would be wise to see an eye doctor to rule out any vision-related issues.
